<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-17BE5A1E-1F83-432B-A7C3-6E2D5D312EEC" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-17BE5A1E-1F83-432B-A7C3-6E2D5D312EEC" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">02 How to remove the pump tube of the ink pump</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_ED1E57E435C04FED8E5EC56505FB661D" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li id="LI_44FE05E8AA614EB29DDDC8E371A37315" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the ink system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="02DISA012" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1C874C66-3A17-4AC4-886B-753A1A37D196.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>02 Open the ink system</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_B00BCB492EC546EE98CD25996779F334" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the rear top cover of the ink system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="02DISA014" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-44A21941-A21F-4C37-A066-3CEA7BE54DAA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>02 How to remove the rear top cover of the ink system</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Close the valves on the Printheads to prevent excessive leaking of ink from the tube. 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_E753369EFDC5426BBE20201BB8995B3D" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_50A196376D55490EAE250E9F76F00C3D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A cloth 
</p></li><li id="LI_CB6A70757D404B7C80E829F47B7447B0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">2 caps to lock the ink tube 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-2954F034-E328-4604-A5AB-9917FAB44242" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><p class="- topic/p ">Only apply grease when both 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">sides</b> of the pump tube are connected to the ink system of the engine. 
</p><fig id="GUID-0284EDF4-1B60-480D-9D00-7470598F8D97" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1CCA11A9-5F57-4E7B-B957-99C0424EBD11-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1CCA11A9-5F57-4E7B-B957-99C0424EBD11-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_02E80458CCD7453CA0EF1FDB3BE8E5D3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table id="TABLE_D003021DEA3B44B68823500D2EF89AF3" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the plastic cap of the ink pump: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Pull with some pressure at the bottom of the cap. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The cap can be removed. 
</p><note id="GUID-194E98E5-6E02-4371-9D3A-48EA7E069DF5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Keep the rollers and rotor assembly in place. 
</p></note></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-A4CEDBA0-579D-4C2D-9159-65C3C35F5FEB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BF35C432-EEBB-45ED-ABBB-E31F30382483-low.jpg" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF35C432-EEBB-45ED-ABBB-E31F30382483-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the pump tube from the pump: hold the rotor in place and remove the pump tube between the rotor and the curved inner surface of the pump base. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place a towel under the working place to catch spilling ink. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_30447A33E4994180B0BD5BF4226741E8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2F80229B-0D18-48F8-B0A2-4DE1A76BD488-low.png" id="IMAGE_834FD2AB3A0941C08CB898D9FDE57673" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2F80229B-0D18-48F8-B0A2-4DE1A76BD488-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the pump tube at both sides. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Mount the red caps on the 2 ink tubes. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In case a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">new</b> pump tube is used: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">grease</b> the new pump tube and axis. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="02ADJU008" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-426D3396-40E9-4911-A828-84C22A061E43.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>02 How to grease the pump tube and axis of the ink pump</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><note id="GUID-5DB0B26B-B94F-4EE4-AD5C-E28411F526FD" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Only apply grease when both 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">sides</b> of the tube are connected to the ink system of the engine. 
</p></note></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Pull out a little bit the rotor of the pump. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Hold the rotor in place and install the pump tube [A] between the rotor and the curved inner surface [B] of the pump base. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-A5B4166A-6E19-4D97-AAEE-845339257410" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9213C29C-276D-4C5C-86EF-FEB5ED951A41-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9213C29C-276D-4C5C-86EF-FEB5ED951A41-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-E86D9AF2-C020-4EEB-B16F-75DFEE9D4AD2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2126515F-D083-45D5-A2E7-48261479969D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2126515F-D083-45D5-A2E7-48261479969D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install the pump cap on the ink pump. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-00E5F137-C696-47D6-B40D-C2D7C8458042" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-274DE93A-45AE-4C05-9480-8F8C0EF65B07-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-274DE93A-45AE-4C05-9480-8F8C0EF65B07-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-B2922812-DDBD-4955-8D33-C0DF464D48D1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-23604701-2671-449E-A800-78B1DAB9D283-low.jpg" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-23604701-2671-449E-A800-78B1DAB9D283-low.jpg"/></fig><fig id="GUID-92957913-DA41-4EF7-A66F-E792B5F5B5B9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-527C11A9-66A2-436B-A763-D7041C9DB99E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-527C11A9-66A2-436B-A763-D7041C9DB99E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the caps and connect the pump tube to both ink tubes, be careful that the internal ink lines, luer couplers are not contaminated with the grease.
</p><note id="GUID-F3BAA289-5BEA-4A32-9D8A-1FAEE333DCDA" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the valves on the Printheads again if you closed them. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Close the ink cabinet. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS02-8-006" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-687A9E42-142D-4818-B5F6-4794D27C8969.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>02-8-006 Operating time ink pump tube [0.1s] (02M1, 02M3, 02M5, 02M7, 02M50, Mxx) [Maintenance Counters]</xref> and reset the value to 0. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Resetting the counter value will make sure the system uses the correct ink flow to dose ink towards the Printheads. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Refill the ink tube that has just been open. This will also remove any air that got into the tube. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use : 
<xref keyref="02ADJU001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-4A9855DA-F3E3-4188-88E5-42BD74907F2D.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>02 How to refill the ink system</xref>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-1CE85252-F6D3-4421-930B-8AE723FFB49C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>